Why are there double links to the webchat? If two links are desirable, it seems better to have the first be an irc:// URI?
IDK why the first one was linked twice, but it looked nice so I followed that. Dropped the first link in both.

I don't think anyone of us can change the title of an unaffiliated channel
While #bitcoin still exists on freenode, it's much quieter than Libera, so this seems reasonable.

Not sure removing this is a good idea.

On one hand, [Noodle] is no longer a Freenode user (the NickServ database got reset)

On the other, it's not clear if this might be a copyright attribution?

Do we have a way to reach [Noodle] and ask?
It was added in 68ba85fd750e94861440ef15047d571d6b518217 / #4317 in 2014 with no other explanation.  Happy to drop the change if people think it's better to keep it.
